### `++fra`

Divide

Produces the quotient of `b` divided by `c`, with `a` as the modular base.

#### Accepts

`a` is an atom.

`b` is an atom.

`c` is an atom.

#### Produces

An atom.

#### Accepts

`a` is an atom.

`b` is an atom.

#### Source

      ++  fra
        |=  [b=@ c=@]
        (pro b (inv c))

#### Examples

    > (~(fra fo 2) 8 2)
    0

    > (~(fra fo 3) 8 2)
    1

    > (~(fra fo 4) 8 2)
    0

    > (~(fra fo 5) 8 2)
    4

