### `++inv`

Inverse

Produces an atom by taking the signed modulus of `a` with the coefficient `u`;
`u` is produced by taking the `++egcd` of `a` and `b`.

#### Accepts

`a` is an atom.

`b` is an atom.

#### Produces

An atom.

#### Source

      ++  inv
        |=  b=@
        =+  c=(dul:si u:(egcd b a) a)
        c

#### Examples

    > (~(inv fo 11) 2)
    6

    > (~(inv fo 71) 255)
    22

    > (~(inv fo 79) 255)
    22

    > (~(inv fo 78) 255)
    67

    > (~(inv fo 70) 255)
    67

